Preheat the oven to 400 degrees. Remove the @shrimp{10%ounce} from the refrigerator
and bring to room temperature. Halve, peel, and thinly slice @red onion{1}.
Roughly chop the @mint{1/4%ounce}(leaves only). Drain and rinse the @cannellini beans{13.4%ounce}. Halve the @grape tomatoes{4%ounce}.

Toss the shrimp on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tablespoon}.
Season with @salt{to taste}, @pepper{to taste}, and as much @chili powder{1%teaspoon} as you like.

Heat a large drizzle of oil in a large #pan{} over medium heat. Add the sliced
onion and cook, tossing, for ~{4-5%minutes}, until softened. Season with salt and
pepper. Add the @spinach{5%ounce} to the pan along with a splash of @water{} and
toss for ~{2-3%minutes}, until the spinach has wilted. Season with salt and pepper,
to taste.

Place the shrimp in the oven for ~{4-7%minutes} until just opaque.

While the shrimp cook, add the beans and tomatoes to the pan over medium heat.
Toss, for ~{2-3%minutes}, until heated through. When the shrimp are ready, add
them to the pan along with half the mint.

Season to taste with salt, pepper, and chili powder, as desired. Garnish with
the @feta cheese{2%ounce} and remaining mint leaves. Enjoy!